jobs_results.title: Mid/Senior iOS Developer (3 months)
jobs_results.description:
ABOUT THE COMPANY:

Join ADDENDUM, a global software development and IT team augmentation firm focusing on fintech, banking, and telco industries. Experience tailored benefits, diverse projects with various tech stacks, and opportunities for growth, freedom, and responsibility you desire.

ABOUT THE ROLE:

Whether you're in the heart of the Baltics or anywhere else, you'll join forces with dedicated professionals in the banking sector. Together, you'll work on exciting projects that focus on advancing and supporting the development of a mobile application. This is a contract-based role for a duration of 3 months.

WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING:
‚Ä¢ Develop high-quality native iOS applications using Swift and/or Objective-C.
‚Ä¢ Design and implement solutions that prioritize performance, security, and outstanding user experience.
‚Ä¢ Stay updated with and apply the latest trends and best practices in user interface and user experience design.
‚Ä¢ Ensure high code quality standards while actively sharing knowledge with the team.

WHAT WE EXPECT:
‚Ä¢ Proven experience in developing native iOS applications.
‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of iOS architecture, design patterns, and best practices for app development.
‚Ä¢ Expertise in creating secure, high-performance solutions focused on user experience (UX) and user interface (UI).
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of modern tools and workflows, including version control systems (e.g., Git) and Agile methodologies.
‚Ä¢ Attention to detail in writing clean, efficient, and well-documented code.
‚Ä¢ Excellent communication skills and a collaborative mindset to share knowledge and contribute to the teams success.

WHAT WE OFFER:

Salary ranges: 20 eur/hour - 40 eur/hour (the given range is flexible and depends on your experience).

At Addendum we believe in personalized benefits packages that cater to your unique passions. Tell us what drives you, and we'll craft a package accordingly. On top of that, heres whats in store automatically:
‚Ä¢ Flexible Hours: No more 9-to-5; work when you're at your best.
‚Ä¢ Top Talent Collaboration: Join award-winning teams from different countries.
‚Ä¢ Diverse, Challenging Projects: Break free from the ordinary with dynamic, stimulating work.
‚Ä¢ Epic Team Events: Join us for summer and winter parties and online events.
‚Ä¢ Special Celebrations: We love a good shindig for birthdays and project milestones.

And if you want to turn up the volume even more, here's what you can additionally have:
‚Ä¢ Rock star Benefits: From health and wellness to tech gadgets, we've got it covered.
‚Ä¢ Flexible Work Options: You choose your work style: from the office to a beach in Bali.
‚Ä¢ Healthy Work-Life Balance: Easy sick-leave and unlimited work-from-home options.

So, get your dancing shoes on and come join the fun!

At ADDENDUM, we wholeheartedly reject all forms of discrimination, including but not limited to age, disability, sex, sexual orientation, pregnancy and maternity, race or ethnicity, religion or belief, gender identity, marriage, civil partnership, or any other protected category. We are committed to fostering a culture of equality and inclusion, where every individual has the opportunity to thrive.

jobs_results.title: Senior iOS Developer
jobs_results.description:
We believe it takes great people to create a great product. That‚Äôs why our team lives our company values, and we hire based on them, too. Since 2010, Pipedrive has been on a mission to support sales and marketing teams with easy-to-use, powerful tools that make everyday work faster and easier. Today, our cloud-based software is trusted by over 100,000 companies and used in 179 countries. We have grown from a five-person team to a truly international company of over 850+ people, representing more than 50 nationalities, with ten offices distributed across Europe and the US. In 2020, Pipedrive received a majority investment from Vista Equity Partners, a global investment firm that invests exclusively in enterprise software, data and technology-enabled businesses, making Pipedrive the fifth unicorn from Estonia.

We‚Äôre looking for a senior iOS developer to collaborate on developing the essential Pipedrive mobile application.

Your new adventure:
‚Ä¢ Manage the entire app lifecycle from ideation to release
‚Ä¢ Strive to create a great user experience
‚Ä¢ Empower engineers to drive both technical and product solutions
‚Ä¢ Work primarily with Swift but maintain some code in Objective-C

Does this sound like you?
‚Ä¢ Proficient in Swift
‚Ä¢ Passionate about iOS development and curious about other technologies
‚Ä¢ A team player with a strong can-do attitude
‚Ä¢ Prioritise people over machines, focus on working on the product rather than just writing pretty code, and design efficient solutions rather than relying on workarounds
‚Ä¢ Drive to create an excellent user experience and build a product that people love to use
‚Ä¢ Capability to deliver flawless features through rigorous testing
‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of patterns, clean code approaches, multithreading, and memory management
‚Ä¢ Ability to guide and motivate the team through leadership and mentoring

Why Pipedrive?
‚Ä¢ A value-driven work environment where people come first
‚Ä¢ A lively bunch of colleagues from over 50 different countries, with offices in Tallinn, Tartu, Lisbon, Prague, London, Dublin, New York, Florida, Riga and Berlin
‚Ä¢ A team serious about getting things done while not taking ourselves too seriously
‚Ä¢ A world-class working environment full of perks like parties, craft workshops, snacks and, of course, office dogs
‚Ä¢ Flexible working hours as long as you‚Äôre there for your team members
‚Ä¢ Freedom to execute your ideas with a passionate and motivated team supporting you
‚Ä¢ Lots of room for personal and career development, with internal and external training opportunities
‚Ä¢ Competitive salary and bonus system and all the benefits you‚Äôd expect from a great employer (health and accident insurance, health days, a quarterly contribution to sports, in-house coaches, employee discounts and more)

Based on this role's access to certain data, Pipedrive might conduct a pre-employment background investigation in conjunction with your application for employment with our company. Such data will be handled in accordance with Pipedrive's Privacy Policy for Recruitment.

Pipedrive is an equal opportunity employer. We encourage diversity in the workplace regardless of age, gender, race, religion, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or veteran status.

We‚Äôre on the lookout for a senior iOS developer to join us in our Tallinn office.

If this is something for you, send us your resume (in English) or a link to your LinkedIn profile and please add why we should pay extra attention to your application.

jobs_results.title: Senior iOS Developer (Remote)
jobs_results.description:
üöÄ What's the position?

This is a Full-time Senior iOS Developer position at Neybox for talented individuals who want to work on cutting-edge applications that positively impact the well-being of individuals worldwide.

üí´ What will I be working on?

You'll be working on our two apps: Pillow, a sleep-tracking app, and Today, which is a quantified-self wellness app.

Both apps have won an Editors' Choice distinction and have been featured multiple times in press and media. They have millions of users worldwide and a great roadmap ahead.

üßë‚Äçüíª What will be my role and responsibilities?

As a senior developer you will be responsible for
‚Ä¢ Building new features
‚Ä¢ Fixing bugs
‚Ä¢ Maintaining the existing codebase
‚Ä¢ Writting Unit Tests for existing and new features
‚Ä¢ Making sure the documentation of the project is accurate and helpful
‚Ä¢ Doing research on new technologies and frameworks
‚Ä¢ ‚ö†Ô∏èThis is a position that requires a commitment of 40 hours per week. This is not a part-time position.

üõ†Ô∏è What's the tech stack?

In a nutshell:

Both our apps are written in Swift (MVVM and MVC).

The UI is written in SwiftUI and UIKit.

We write Unit Tests; the code is clean and well-documented.

We make extensive use of various frameworks and machine learning.

Both apps are available for iOS only.

üåç Can I work remotely?

Of course! Our team is 100% remote. We have flexible working hours, but a good overlap between our time zones is required.

üôå What is it like working at Neybox?

Our team is small by design (6-8 people). However, we work closely together every day (Mon-Fri). For coordination, we use Slack and Jira and keep meetings at a minimum.

There's no middle management to get in the way, and we encourage new ideas and close collaboration.

üíº What are the requirements?
‚Ä¢ 4+ years of iOS development experience in Swift
‚Ä¢ Experience in HealthKit, CoreML SwiftUI, UIKit, Core Animation, GCD, Core Data, and WatchKit.
‚Ä¢ Experience working with Git version control, Unit testing, and Continuous Integration
‚Ä¢ Experience in performance profiling with Instruments on Xcode.
‚Ä¢ Proficient use of English, both writing and speaking.
‚Ä¢ Willingness to learn and experiment with new technologies.
‚Ä¢ References from previous employers in written or spoken form may be required from previous employers.
‚Ä¢ Proficient in usage of MacOS and iOS.

üì• Great! How can I apply?

Just hit "Apply" button below!

‚ö†Ô∏è Please note that this is the only acceptable way to apply. All other ways of contacting Neybox about the position (social media, LinkedIn, email etc.), will result in immediate rejection.

jobs_results.title: Mobile Developer - iOS - Spend & Wise Platform
jobs_results.description:
Wise is one the fastest growing companies in Europe and we‚Äôre on a mission: to make money without borders the new normal. We‚Äôve got 10 million customers across the globe and that number is growing. Fast.

Current financial systems don‚Äôt let us send, spend or receive money across borders easily. Or quickly. Or cheaply.

So, we‚Äôve been building a new one.

We are looking for iOS engineers at all levels to join our mission and help provide our customers with the best mobile experience possible.

We work in small, autonomous cross-functional teams. Team members own the problems and provide best in class solutions for our customers.

The Wise card is a key part of the borderless proposition, it is responsible for the "spend" part of the general vision. Card issuing is the best way to let customers spend their money in the modern world, but we should keep in mind that real plastic cards are only one of a possible solution to spending problems. Tomorrow it could be virtual cards, apple and google pays, QR codes, mobile payments, or something else that is not yet invented. Our mission statement for the Spend & Wise tribe is: Give our customers reliable, easy to use and eventually free way to pay from borderless accounts everywhere in the world.

What does it take?
‚Ä¢ Experience with building iOS apps that delight users
‚Ä¢ Thinking from the customer perspective and putting them at the heart of everything you do
‚Ä¢ A passion for product quality and user experience, attention to detail
‚Ä¢ Knowledgeable about product engineering (or have the desire to learn it) <https://tech.transferwise.com/product-engineering-principles-transferwise/>
‚Ä¢ Ability to both collaborate effectively with your team and solve problems independently and proactively
‚Ä¢ Great communication skills and the ability to articulate complex, technical concepts to non-technical audiences
‚Ä¢ Full-stack iOS development (we work in small teams, each with one or two mobile engineers, it‚Äôs likely you‚Äôll be in charge of a feature from API to UI)
‚Ä¢ Know SOLID ways to implement clean architecture, writing readable code that is testable (we currently work with VIPER but are continuously evaluating the latest architectures/methodologies - SwiftUI and Combine are nice to have)
‚Ä¢ We value experience with state-of-art technologies, but we value eagerness to learn them even more

What the first six months look like?
‚Ä¢ You‚Äôll have on-boarded and found your place by understanding your team and guild vision and how you can contribute
‚Ä¢ You‚Äôll have an understanding of your team‚Äôs domain and our tech culture
‚Ä¢ You‚Äôll have fully shipped new features, from planning to release, and kept monitoring their adoption once live
‚Ä¢ You‚Äôll have gone through two quarterly plannings and proposed ideas to take our product further

What you get back?
‚Ä¢ The autonomy to solve problems your way
‚Ä¢ The freedom to have real impact
‚Ä¢ Loads of development opportunities
‚Ä¢ A fun work environment with social activities and events

And more‚Ä¶ Check out our offer here.

Interested? Find out more:
‚Ä¢ How we work - a practical guide
‚Ä¢ TransferWise Vlogs: Omar, Engineering Lead
‚Ä¢ Engineering team blog
‚Ä¢ How our Engineers build new features

We‚Äôre people without borders ‚Äî without judgement or prejudice, too. We want to work with the best people, no matter their background. So if you‚Äôre passionate about learning new things and keen to join our mission, you‚Äôll fit right in.

Also, where and what you studied isn't important to us. If you‚Äôve got great experience, the right skills for the role and you‚Äôre great at articulating your thinking, we‚Äôd like to hear from you.

jobs_results.title: Support Engineer (iOS/Xcode team)
jobs_results.description:
Hi, I‚Äôm Nihal Aghazada, Customer Engineering lead at Codemagic.

I‚Äôm looking for a Support Engineer with experience building and publishing iOS apps with Xcode to join the Codemagic team to make our customers more successful with our product.

We serve tens of thousands of software engineers and work with some of the most talented mobile teams in the world.

As an Support Engineer in the iOS/Xcode team at Codemagic, you are the first point of contact for our customers and you will be helping them set up new CI/CD pipelines and also assist with scripting and debugging.

As you grow into the role you will become a CI/CD expert and your knowledge will help us steer our product development in a way that directly benefits our customers.

The position is remote-friendly and open to candidates within a 4-hour time difference to Estonia (UTC+3)

About us

Our core mission is to give developers actionable feedback and make releasing mobile apps much easier. It‚Äôs a nightmare to release apps today and we can change that. We partnered with Google in 2018 to bring Codemagic to market and have since gained the support of the developer community and grown into a community favorite CI/CD.

See how we compare with the competition here. We have a great fit with one market segment - Flutter developers and we are expanding our product to new segments.

As we grow we realize all of this is possible thanks to the support from our community, customers, partners, and of course, the incredible people working here.

Meaningful work you‚Äôll contribute:
‚Ä¢ Help developers via Intercom, email, Discord, and video call
‚Ä¢ Identify the root cause of issues and determine whether they are bugs, configuration issues, or third-party errors
‚Ä¢ Propose solutions and fix bugs either yourself or with the help of other engineers
‚Ä¢ Help improve our product documentation
‚Ä¢ Write 'Codemagic Rocks!' in your cover letter to show that you pay attention.
‚Ä¢ Collaborating with the Product and Marketing departments

Valuable experiences and skills you‚Äôll bring to Codemagic
‚Ä¢ Previous experience with mobile development (Flutter, React Native, iOS, Android)
‚Ä¢ Experience with publishing apps to the Apple App Store
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with configuring iOS apps in Xcode
‚Ä¢ Good bash skills and hands-on experience with CI/CD
‚Ä¢ Interest in developer tools
‚Ä¢ Passion for creative problem-solving
‚Ä¢ Empathy and love for working with customers
‚Ä¢ Previous experience in customer-facing roles
‚Ä¢ Visa Sponsorship

Please note, this position is not eligible for visa sponsorship.

Our culture

Our culture is built on transparency, diversity, meritocracy, and support ‚Äî and we seek people who are resilient, entrepreneurial-minded, team players who continually strive to be incrementally better every single day. In our work together we aim to be curious, accountable, empathetic, and, above all, collaborative. If this sounds like the environment you‚Äôd thrive in, why not say hello?

The position is full-time either from our HQ in Tartu, Estonia, or remotely from other parts of the world (preferably +-4h time difference)

Applying

Send us your CV and tell us about yourself and the experience you have with publishing iOS apps to the App Store.

Cheers,

Nihal
